Prime Minister Kishida and President Biden met in Hiroshima, Japan, ahead of the G7 Summit. They emphasized the strong relationship between Japan and the United States and discussed various areas of cooperation, including security, innovation, and emerging technologies. They also expressed their commitment to upholding the free and open international order based on the rule of law. President Biden thanked Japan for its support in addressing global challenges and reiterated the importance of standing together for a safer world.